- Huh?

68
00:05:01.619 --> 00:05:03.920
No. No. um...

69
00:05:03.955 --> 00:05:05.722
You were fine.

70
00:05:05.757 --> 00:05:07.423
You were more than fine.

71
00:05:07.459 --> 00:05:10.193
15 minutes... That should be
time for a cup of coffee.

72
00:05:10.228 --> 00:05:11.728
I saw a machine downstairs.

73
00:05:11.763 --> 00:05:13.262
I'm Eddie.

74
00:05:13.298 --> 00:05:15.698
Um. Zed.

75
00:05:15.734 --> 00:05:18.668
I'm sorry. I... I... I have to go.

76
00:05:18.703 --> 00:05:21.437
Oh. okay. Um... What about dinner?

77
00:05:21.473 --> 00:05:24.607
- You know what? I... really. I don't...
- Eat?

78
00:05:28.046 --> 00:05:29.879
Uh...

79
00:05:35.453 --> 00:05:37.620
Giancarlo's.

80
00:05:37.655 --> 00:05:39.922
Thursday. 7:00 P.M.

81
00:05:39.958 --> 00:05:41.224
Okay.

82
00:05:44.360 --> 00:05:46.493
John. I just had this insane vision.

83
00:05:46.563 --> 00:05:47.120
Oh. how are you. John?

84
00:05:47.145 --> 00:05:48.563
I didn't have to touch
anything to have the vision.

85
00:05:48.598 --> 00:05:49.398
Well. actually. I have a
little bit of a bad neck

86
00:05:49.399 --> 00:05:51.431
- And I swore it was real.
- I slept a bit awkward last night...

87
00:05:51.696 --> 00:05:52.929
I mean. I saw these snakes
crawling up my leg.

88
00:05:52.997 --> 00:05:54.496
and one of those snakes
actually went up and bit my leg.

89
00:05:54.524 --> 00:05:55.956
What. you said snakes?

90
00:05:55.992 --> 00:05:57.558
Yeah.

91
00:05:57.593 --> 00:05:59.860
Our training is expanding
your psychic awareness.

92
00:05:59.896 --> 00:06:01.262
You see there?

93
00:06:02.331 --> 00:06:03.531
What. Kentucky?

94
00:06:03.566 --> 00:06:04.999
Middle of bugger all.

95
00:06:05.034 --> 00:06:07.334
Seems a preacher was bit

96
00:06:07.370 --> 00:06:09.470
by a poisonous snake.
which explains your vision.

97
00:06:09.505 --> 00:06:11.639
He came back to life.
started performing miracles.

98
00:06:11.674 --> 00:06:13.141
and now...

99
00:06:13.177 --> 00:06:14.643
He's a bloody star.

100
00:06:15.846 --> 00:06:18.213
This is from a conspiracy web site.

101
00:06:18.249 --> 00:06:20.049
Nabbed this bad boy

102
00:06:20.084 --> 00:06:21.617
off the grim reaper himself.

103
00:06:21.652 --> 00:06:23.552
it says that he regrew a man's leg.

104
00:06:23.588 --> 00:06:25.054
Yeah. I saw lots

105
00:06:25.089 --> 00:06:27.089
of these cons growing up.
Oh. yeah. and. uh.

106
00:06:27.124 --> 00:06:28.390
where was that exactly?

107
00:06:28.426 --> 00:06:30.960
- Uh-uh.
- Hmm.

108
00:06:30.995 --> 00:06:34.229
Well. I must have protection.

109
00:06:34.265 --> 00:06:35.664
Of various kinds.

110
00:06:35.700 --> 00:06:38.534
We're gonna go visit
a preacher in a church?

111
00:06:39.637 --> 00:06:42.137
That's a good point.

112
00:06:43.608 --> 00:06:45.641
So. Chas is off duty.

113
00:06:45.676 --> 00:06:47.610
He's making good with his daughter.

114
00:06:47.645 --> 00:06:49.612
Guess what that means.

115
00:06:49.647 --> 00:06:51.580
You're driving.

116
00:06:51.616 --> 00:06:53.248
Grab my coat. will you?

117
00:06:53.284 --> 00:06:57.252
In my name shall they cast out.

118
00:06:57.288 --> 00:06:59.989
They shall...

119
00:07:00.024 --> 00:07:01.991
Lay hands on the sick.

120
00:07:02.026 --> 00:07:04.159
and they shall...

121
00:07:04.195 --> 00:07:06.362
Excuse me. luv.

122
00:07:06.397 --> 00:07:09.164
Many of you have traveled

123
00:07:09.200 --> 00:07:12.368
a great distance to be here this...

124
00:07:12.403 --> 00:07:14.436
Beautiful Sunday morning

125
00:07:14.472 --> 00:07:16.105
the lord has gifted us!

126
00:07:16.140 --> 00:07:18.107
We done with the boring part yet?

127
00:07:18.142 --> 00:07:19.808
And I know...

128
00:07:19.844 --> 00:07:23.012
This is the part y'all been waiting for.

129
00:07:24.081 --> 00:07:27.549
Your faith has been rewarded.

130
00:07:27.585 --> 00:07:30.486
God has come to grace us.

131
00:07:30.521 --> 00:07:33.322
and today you shall witness his power.

132
00:07:33.357 --> 00:07:35.791
And let me tell you.

133
00:07:35.826 --> 00:07:36.892
it is great!

134
00:07:36.927 --> 00:07:38.694
Can you feel it?

135
00:07:40.698 --> 00:07:43.399
I can feel the power of God!

136
00:07:48.072 --> 00:07:50.372
I invite you to be healed.

137
00:07:53.544 --> 00:07:55.511
I can s-see.

138
00:07:57.448 --> 00:07:58.914
This is just ridiculous.

139
00:07:58.949 --> 00:08:00.649
You brought me here for this?

140
00:08:00.685 --> 00:08:02.351
You brought me here... your vision.

141
00:08:02.386 --> 00:08:04.053
if I recall correctly.

142
00:08:04.088 --> 00:08:06.588
They're all so hungry
for something to believe in.

143
00:08:06.624 --> 00:08:08.190
He's just preying on them.

144
00:08:08.225 --> 00:08:10.659
Yeah. well. suckers make easy prey.

145
00:08:10.695 --> 00:08:12.061
They're not suckers.

146
00:08:12.096 --> 00:08:13.829
They're just not jaded like you.

147
00:08:13.864 --> 00:08:16.065
They're still searching
for the magic in their lives.

148
00:08:16.100 --> 00:08:18.333
Didn't take you for a religious one.

149
00:08:18.369 --> 00:08:20.369
I don't know what I am...

150
00:08:20.404 --> 00:08:24.339
But I like to believe there's
a... guiding hand in it all.

151
00:08:24.375 --> 00:08:26.709
Guiding... judging...

152
00:08:26.744 --> 00:08:28.377
Damning.

153
00:08:28.412 --> 00:08:30.345
He's a jack of all trades. really.

154
00:08:30.381 --> 00:08:32.181
I mean. I'm not critiquing or anything.

155
00:08:32.216 --> 00:08:34.850
but I'm pretty sure
he's not very keen on me.

156
00:08:37.588 --> 00:08:39.888
in his name...

157
00:08:39.924 --> 00:08:42.224
I heal you.

158
00:08:48.799 --> 00:08:51.300
Still think we came to the wrong place?

159
00:09:02.079 --> 00:09:04.413
That's Enochian.

160
00:09:04.448 --> 00:09:06.915
The language of the bloody angels.

161
00:09:08.152 --> 00:09:10.285
Angels... They really exist?

162
00:09:10.321 --> 00:09:11.920
Unfortunately. yes.

163
00:09:11.956 --> 00:09:13.922
I don't speak their lingo.

164
00:09:13.958 --> 00:09:16.892
but I recognize the sound.
Have you met one?

165
00:09:16.927 --> 00:09:19.495
Let's just table the angel talk. luv.

166
00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:21.396
it's the preacher we need to focus on here.

167
00:09:21.432 --> 00:09:25.334
Nobody wields that kind
of power without consequences.

168
00:09:25.369 --> 00:09:28.837
I got to tell you. doc. it
happened right before my eyes.

169
00:09:29.874 --> 00:09:31.373
Remarkable.

170
00:09:38.015 --> 00:09:39.481
it's getting kind of hot in here.

171
00:09:39.517 --> 00:09:41.517
Yeah. we're almost done. Nate.

172
00:09:41.552 --> 00:09:44.119
Briarwood Med sent me your.
uh. scans from two years ago.

173
00:09:44.155 --> 00:09:46.789
Uh. they'd rushed you into their
ER as a result of. what was it?

174
00:09:46.824 --> 00:09:48.457
A trucking accident.

175
00:09:48.492 --> 00:09:49.758
Trucking accident.

176
00:09:49.794 --> 00:09:51.760
Your leg was crushed. nerves severed.

177
00:09:51.796 --> 00:09:53.462
And then look at today's scans.

178
00:09:53.497 --> 00:09:56.431
The bone has regenerated. the
skin. the tissue. everything.

179
00:09:56.467 --> 00:09:58.167
if I hadn't seen all your other scans.

180
00:09:58.202 --> 00:10:00.102
I'd swear you were a different man.

181
00:10:00.137 --> 00:10:01.703
All right.

182
00:10:04.141 --> 00:10:06.108
All right. and just look into my left ear.

183
00:10:06.143 --> 00:10:07.876
Now. open your eyes for me.

184
00:10:19.990 --> 00:10:21.990
Nate.

185
00:10:53.436 --> 00:10:54.336
Here.

186
00:10:56.036 --> 00:10:58.070
"Commerce at God's door."

187
00:10:58.136 --> 00:10:59.936
Makes me feel all bright and

188
00:10:59.971 --> 00:11:02.371
- shiny.
- Oh. I just love your accent.

189
00:11:02.407 --> 00:11:03.206
You're not from around here.

190
00:11:03.207 --> 00:11:05.141
Sharp tack. you are. luv.

191
00:11:05.176 --> 00:11:07.610
Liverpool. England.
But. uh. I'm well traveled.

192
00:11:07.645 --> 00:11:08.944
Yeah. we drove in from. uh.

193
00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:11.080
Tennessee about a week and a half ago.

194
00:11:11.115 --> 00:11:12.348
Uh. preacher Zachary. he cleared

195
00:11:12.383 --> 00:11:13.649
Nancy's chronic arthritis

196
00:11:13.684 --> 00:11:14.917
with just a touch.

197
00:11:14.952 --> 00:11:16.352
Pain-free.

198
00:11:16.387 --> 00:11:18.020
Are you going down to the river tomorrow?

199
00:11:18.056 --> 00:11:19.622
There's a group Baptism.

200
00:11:19.657 --> 00:11:22.158
Well. I tell you what.
I fancy a dip right now.

201
00:11:24.729 --> 00:11:27.029
What's your name. darling?

202
00:11:27.065 --> 00:11:29.532
Zed.

203
00:11:29.567 --> 00:11:30.900
Give me your hands.

204
00:11:33.404 --> 00:11:35.137
You have doubt.

205
00:11:35.173 --> 00:11:36.839
Inside.

206
00:11:36.874 --> 00:11:38.808
I have a good reason to doubt.

207
00:11:38.843 --> 00:11:41.110
But you want to believe.

208
00:11:41.145 --> 00:11:43.179
I can see that.

209
00:12:02.233 --> 00:12:04.233
May God bless your soul.

210
00:12:09.841 --> 00:12:11.707
Oh. no. I've. uh...

211
00:12:11.742 --> 00:12:13.676
Got a bit of a cold. actually.

212
00:12:13.711 --> 00:12:15.044
Wouldn't want to make you sick.

213
00:12:15.079 --> 00:12:18.147
But thanks. anyway.

214
00:12:18.182 --> 00:12:20.149
What can I do for you?

215
00:12:20.184 --> 00:12:21.550
Just a quick question.

216
00:12:21.586 --> 00:12:24.820
Where did you learn the Enochian you spoke?

217
00:12:24.856 --> 00:12:26.388
Pardon me?

218
00:12:26.424 --> 00:12:27.756
Enochian.

219
00:12:29.127 --> 00:12:31.827
It's the language of the angels.

220
00:12:31.863 --> 00:12:34.230
You spoke it in your sermon this morning.

221
00:12:34.265 --> 00:12:37.566
Who are we to question the gifts
we receive from the Lord?

222
00:12:37.602 --> 00:12:40.302
God bless your soul.

223
00:13:23.247 --> 00:13:24.813
Aah!

224
00:13:35.960 --> 00:13:38.294
I could feel him. John.

225
00:13:38.329 --> 00:13:39.995
He was so close to death.

226
00:13:40.031 --> 00:13:42.131
I felt what he felt in that moment.

227
00:13:42.166 --> 00:13:43.899
An angel. So you said.

228
00:13:43.935 --> 00:13:45.768
Thanks. mate.

229
00:13:45.803 --> 00:13:48.604
Just about the only thing around
here that isn't deep fried.

230
00:13:48.639 --> 00:13:52.074
So you get any other sense of
Zachary the great and powerful?

231
00:13:52.109 --> 00:13:54.076
Well. he has good intentions

232
00:13:54.111 --> 00:13:56.312
and he's unquestioning in his faith.

233
00:13:56.347 --> 00:13:58.647
Bit boring. but okay.

234
00:13:58.683 --> 00:14:01.917
Let's say he's not the dark
part of this equation.

235
00:14:01.953 --> 00:14:04.186
Unless he's being manipulated.

236
00:14:04.222 --> 00:14:07.022
Blind faith can be a dangerous thing.

237
00:14:07.058 --> 00:14:09.458
Spoken from experience?

238
00:14:12.797 --> 00:14:15.130
Maybe what the preacher's
doing is legitimate.

239
00:14:15.166 --> 00:14:16.932
From what I read. Briarwood went through

240
00:14:16.968 --> 00:14:18.534
a pretty rough drought this past year.

241
00:14:18.569 --> 00:14:19.969
Everyone's trying to make ends meet.

242
00:14:20.004 --> 00:14:21.637
Maybe these people get
to have their miracles.

243
00:14:21.672 --> 00:14:23.606
Well. miracles are ours to make. luv.

244
00:14:23.641 --> 00:14:26.842
And your visions are connected
to the scry map. remember?

245
00:14:26.877 --> 00:14:29.345
Scry map bad.

246
00:14:29.380 --> 00:14:31.847
But his heart is in the right place.

247
00:14:31.882 --> 00:14:34.183
Well. I can't speak to that.

248
00:14:34.218 --> 00:14:37.019
but I can speak to his magic.

249
00:14:37.054 --> 00:14:39.488
it's much too powerful.

250
00:14:39.523 --> 00:14:42.858
All this healing energy... it
has to come from somewhere.

251
00:14:42.893 --> 00:14:45.828
if history's any indication. then

252
00:14:45.863 --> 00:14:48.998
it'll be taking its toll
on the land already.

253
00:14:49.033 --> 00:14:51.333
On the land?

254
00:14:51.369 --> 00:14:53.902
Follow me.

255
00:14:55.906 --> 00:14:57.906
I thought I smelled something.

256
00:15:02.246 --> 00:15:05.180
Pobrecitos.

257
00:15:05.216 --> 00:15:07.049
What's happening in the church

258
00:15:07.084 --> 00:15:09.084
is a front for something dark.

259
00:15:09.120 --> 00:15:11.020
something poisonous.

260
00:15:11.055 --> 00:15:12.521
And we need to find out

261
00:15:12.556 --> 00:15:14.523
what before that poison spreads.

262
00:15:16.460 --> 00:15:17.793
Manny.

263
00:15:19.563 --> 00:15:21.063
Manny.

264
00:15:21.098 --> 00:15:22.097
Who's Manny?

265
00:15:22.133 --> 00:15:23.565
He's an angel.

266
00:15:23.601 --> 00:15:25.501
So you do know one.

267
00:15:25.536 --> 00:15:27.069
Can I meet him?

268
00:15:27.104 --> 00:15:29.605
No. no. you wipe that look
of wonder off your face.

269
00:15:29.640 --> 00:15:32.608
This one isn't as awe-inspiring
as the title suggests.

270
00:15:32.643 --> 00:15:34.710
Are you kidding me?

271
00:15:34.745 --> 00:15:36.612
With all the darkness
and all the scary stuff

272
00:15:36.647 --> 00:15:38.113
in the world of John Constantine.

273
00:15:38.149 --> 00:15:39.848
finally there's something light?

274
00:15:39.884 --> 00:15:42.451
Manny!

275
00:15:42.486 --> 00:15:45.854
Maybe if you asked nicer.

276
00:16:05.242 --> 00:16:08.210
Do you see all those people out there?

277
00:16:08.245 --> 00:16:10.212
We're gonna need to build a bigger church.

278
00:16:10.247 --> 00:16:13.148
Yeah. it's amazing.

279
00:16:13.184 --> 00:16:16.318
I hear there's one family come
all the way from Poughkeepsie.

280
00:16:16.354 --> 00:16:19.655
You... you think maybe we
ought to slow down a little?

281
00:16:19.690 --> 00:16:22.291
Just try to...

282
00:16:22.326 --> 00:16:24.493
Figure out exactly what
we got on our hands?

283
00:16:24.528 --> 00:16:26.628
it's not our place to question the gift.

284
00:16:26.664 --> 00:16:29.064
Where's my pen? I got a sermon to write.

285
00:16:29.100 --> 00:16:30.966
it's just... we don't know
where it comes from.

286
00:16:31.001 --> 00:16:32.301
Sarah.

287
00:16:32.336 --> 00:16:34.570
I almost died.

288
00:16:34.605 --> 00:16:36.638
But I didn't.

289
00:16:36.674 --> 00:16:38.607
God wants this.

290
00:16:38.642 --> 00:16:42.511
And he's using me to do it.

291
00:16:42.546 --> 00:16:45.247
Or maybe it's daddy
shining down on us from heaven.

292
00:16:45.282 --> 00:16:48.183
Whatever the case. our path is clear.

293
00:16:55.126 --> 00:16:58.327
All right. you wanker.

294
00:17:00.531 --> 00:17:02.531
You won't come the easy way...

295
00:17:04.135 --> 00:17:07.202
I am bringing out the big guns.

296
00:17:07.238 --> 00:17:09.705
You're going to lure an angel with drugs?

297
00:17:09.740 --> 00:17:11.640
it's dried myrtle. luv.

298
00:17:18.582 --> 00:17:21.884
By the divine power that holds the balance.

299
00:17:21.919 --> 00:17:24.119
bring forth your servant

300
00:17:24.155 --> 00:17:26.054
of ministering.

301
00:17:26.090 --> 00:17:28.190
By your wisdom and your justice.

302
00:17:28.225 --> 00:17:30.759
your will be done.

303
00:17:32.730 --> 00:17:34.062
Please.

304
00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:37.833
That was a nice touch.

305
00:17:37.868 --> 00:17:39.735
Won't make the slightest bit
of difference. luv.

306
00:17:43.274 --> 00:17:45.140
On the contrary. the girl's right...

307
00:17:45.176 --> 00:17:47.910
Courtesy counts.

308
00:17:50.080 --> 00:17:52.848
What. you want to hear me beg. is that it?

309
00:17:52.883 --> 00:17:54.383
Reminds me of an ex-girlfriend

310
00:17:54.418 --> 00:17:56.752
of mine. I do have other
mortals to watch over.

311
00:17:56.787 --> 00:17:58.153
John.

312
00:17:58.189 --> 00:17:59.488
I don't want you to watch.

313
00:17:59.523 --> 00:18:01.223
I want you to listen.

314
00:18:01.258 --> 00:18:04.026
There's a preacher in town...

315
00:18:04.061 --> 00:18:06.862
He's using some pretty powerful magic.

316
00:18:06.897 --> 00:18:09.264
So I can see. He's speaking

317
00:18:09.300 --> 00:18:11.533
in Enochian tongues.

318
00:18:13.237 --> 00:18:15.037
I need to know what he's saying.

319
00:18:15.072 --> 00:18:18.907
it would only make sense
if you stand facing the sun.

320
00:18:20.578 --> 00:18:23.278
You just... love a good riddle.

321
00:18:23.314 --> 00:18:26.181
don't you? Look. I'm a
foot past the line. John.

322
00:18:26.217 --> 00:18:28.550
You know I cannot

323
00:18:28.586 --> 00:18:31.053
sway the outcome of events.

324
00:18:31.088 --> 00:18:32.955
All right.

325
00:18:32.990 --> 00:18:35.290
While I face the sun.

326
00:18:35.326 --> 00:18:36.725
Then what?

327
00:18:36.760 --> 00:18:38.827
What good is it really gonna... oh.

328
00:18:40.431 --> 00:18:42.598
Bollocks. Not much of a guardian

329
00:18:42.633 --> 00:18:44.867
angel if he's not here
when you want him. huh?

330
00:18:44.902 --> 00:18:48.136
No. he got his point across.
Come here. Do me a favor. luv.

331
00:18:48.172 --> 00:18:50.105
Hum that tune you heard today.

332
00:18:50.140 --> 00:18:51.373
The Enochian.

333
00:18:51.408 --> 00:18:52.741
What for?

334
00:18:52.776 --> 00:18:56.111
Just... humor me.

335
00:19:20.271 --> 00:19:21.937
Do you hear that?

336
00:19:21.972 --> 00:19:23.972
Yeah.

337
00:19:26.210 --> 00:19:28.210
Echolocation.

338
00:19:33.784 --> 00:19:35.784
it's getting louder.

339
00:19:38.789 --> 00:19:40.255
There.

340
00:19:40.291 --> 00:19:42.357
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. easy.
Careful. careful.

341
00:19:55.906 --> 00:19:58.006
Ay. dios mío.

342
00:20:06.309 --> 00:20:07.809
It looks abandoned.

343
00:20:07.845 --> 00:20:09.845
We should be safe here for now.

344
00:20:09.880 --> 00:20:11.880
Over there.

345
00:20:13.684 --> 00:20:15.284
Here. take her. Yeah. yeah.

346
00:20:22.660 --> 00:20:24.660
Here you are. luv.

347
00:20:40.911 --> 00:20:42.277
She's an actual angel.

348
00:20:42.313 --> 00:20:43.712
is this the one you know?

349
00:20:43.747 --> 00:20:45.681
No. this one's a lot prettier.

350
00:20:45.716 --> 00:20:47.382
I'm Imogen.

351
00:20:47.418 --> 00:20:49.017
What happened to you. luv?

352
00:20:49.053 --> 00:20:51.620
I was taking a dying mortal to heaven.

353
00:20:51.655 --> 00:20:53.622
I don't know how. but...

354
00:20:53.657 --> 00:20:56.391
He pulled a feather from my wing.

355
00:20:56.427 --> 00:20:59.127
He was revived.

356
00:20:59.163 --> 00:21:01.129
I fell to earth.

357
00:21:01.165 --> 00:21:04.132
That must be what I saw in my vision
when I touched Zachary.

358
00:21:04.168 --> 00:21:06.401
it's the only way an angel
can enter our plane

359
00:21:06.437 --> 00:21:10.005
in physical form. Damage to the wings.

360
00:21:10.040 --> 00:21:11.840
One feather.

361
00:21:11.875 --> 00:21:15.711
Piss poor design. if you ask me.

362
00:21:15.746 --> 00:21:18.146
That's what Zachary has.

363
00:21:18.182 --> 00:21:19.948
An angel's feather.

364
00:21:22.553 --> 00:21:23.785
Piqued your interest now. have we?

365
00:21:26.523 --> 00:21:27.823
Who are you talking to?

366
00:21:27.858 --> 00:21:29.858
The ugly one.

367
00:21:31.362 --> 00:21:33.528
Where is he?

368
00:21:35.232 --> 00:21:36.431
Are you okay?

369
00:21:36.467 --> 00:21:39.067
I don't know.

370
00:21:39.103 --> 00:21:40.702
Everything hurts.

371
00:21:40.738 --> 00:21:42.204
You could've helped me find her faster.

372
00:21:42.239 --> 00:21:44.106
you know. Is he over here?

373
00:21:44.141 --> 00:21:46.375
I didn't know she fell. John.

374
00:21:46.410 --> 00:21:48.010
Angels are compartmentalized.

375
00:21:48.045 --> 00:21:50.946
All part of the plan to
prevent our interference.

376
00:21:50.981 --> 00:21:53.115
keep humanity's free will intact.

377
00:21:53.150 --> 00:21:54.283
A little to your right. luv.

378
00:21:54.318 --> 00:21:57.586
Are riddles and...

379
00:21:57.621 --> 00:22:00.756
Minimally helpful guidance
also part of the plan?

380
00:22:00.791 --> 00:22:03.525
A mortal has never been able

381
00:22:03.560 --> 00:22:05.594
to remove an angel's feather before.

382
00:22:05.629 --> 00:22:08.597
Imogen doesn't belong here. She won't last.

383
00:22:08.632 --> 00:22:11.233
Ask him if an angel can die.

384
00:22:11.268 --> 00:22:14.069
Yes.

385
00:22:14.104 --> 00:22:16.471
The soul is extinguished.

386
00:22:16.507 --> 00:22:20.509
We simply cease to exist.

387
00:22:25.082 --> 00:22:27.249
We need to get that feather back.

388
00:22:31.021 --> 00:22:33.822
- What is this?
- Protection spell.

389
00:22:33.857 --> 00:22:36.658
Once I'm done. evil will not
be able to cross the line

390
00:22:36.694 --> 00:22:38.460
created by the flowing water.

391
00:22:38.495 --> 00:22:40.329
Should keep Imogen safe
while we get the feather back

392
00:22:40.364 --> 00:22:41.596
from Zachary.

393
00:22:41.632 --> 00:22:43.098
I should stay.

394
00:22:43.133 --> 00:22:44.766
She's gonna be alone.

395
00:22:44.802 --> 00:22:46.268
She's not alone. luv.

396
00:22:46.303 --> 00:22:48.637
Manny.

397
00:22:48.672 --> 00:22:50.072
How come I can't see him?

398
00:22:50.107 --> 00:22:51.807
He's in spirit form.

399
00:22:51.842 --> 00:22:54.776
He reveals himself to me.
principally to annoy me.

400
00:22:54.812 --> 00:22:56.178
I'm convinced.

401
00:22:56.213 --> 00:22:58.780
But Imogen fell to earth.

402
00:22:58.816 --> 00:23:03.185
She entered the mortal plane.
so she's corporeal.

403
00:23:03.220 --> 00:23:05.153
That's why we can both see her.

404
00:23:05.189 --> 00:23:07.122
You're gobsmacked. aren't you?

405
00:23:08.158 --> 00:23:11.460
I just...

406
00:23:11.495 --> 00:23:14.129
I believed everything I was told as a girl.

407
00:23:14.164 --> 00:23:16.465
The older I got...

408
00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:18.500
The more lies I uncovered.

409
00:23:18.535 --> 00:23:20.435
But angels here? I mean...

410
00:23:20.471 --> 00:23:22.938
I have so many questions
I want to ask them.

411
00:23:22.973 --> 00:23:24.172
Good luck with that. luv.

412
00:23:24.208 --> 00:23:26.174
They're real cagey types.

413
00:23:26.210 --> 00:23:28.210
What do you need them to tell you?

414
00:23:28.245 --> 00:23:31.046
Where my powers come from. for starters.

415
00:23:31.081 --> 00:23:34.149
I mean. do they come from God
or somewhere else?

416
00:23:34.184 --> 00:23:35.984
Doesn't matter where they came from.

417
00:23:36.019 --> 00:23:38.553
What matters is what you do with them

418
00:23:38.589 --> 00:23:40.722
and what it costs you.

419
00:23:40.758 --> 00:23:43.392
You act like religion is for suckers.

420
00:23:43.427 --> 00:23:45.394
but there it is.

421
00:23:45.429 --> 00:23:47.028
Evidence.

422
00:23:47.064 --> 00:23:48.630
How can you still be so cynical?

423
00:23:48.665 --> 00:23:51.032
Oh. wouldn't it be lovely if I wasn't?

424
00:23:51.068 --> 00:23:53.235
Could've been a better man
if I hadn't seen it all.

425
00:23:53.270 --> 00:23:55.337
Yes. angels exist.

426
00:23:55.372 --> 00:23:56.905
Sound the bloody trumpets.

427
00:23:56.940 --> 00:23:59.574
As for religion. yeah. all right.

428
00:23:59.610 --> 00:24:01.576
be nice to your neighbor
and all that. but...

429
00:24:01.612 --> 00:24:04.312
The world isn't all puppy dogs
and rainbows.

430
00:24:04.348 --> 00:24:06.715
Can't just pray evil away.

431
00:24:06.750 --> 00:24:09.217
Still have to fight. hard.

432
00:24:09.253 --> 00:24:11.319
on our own.

433
00:24:11.355 --> 00:24:13.088
Akasha. mi geill

434
00:24:13.123 --> 00:24:14.089
mo prana ri sibh.

435
00:24:32.142 --> 00:24:34.443
Says he's looking for Nate Byars.

436
00:24:34.478 --> 00:24:37.779
Nate Byars? What for?

437
00:24:37.815 --> 00:24:39.448
He's a murder suspect.

438
00:24:39.483 --> 00:24:41.416
Says he killed a police officer.

439
00:24:41.452 --> 00:24:43.118
And a doctor just outside of town.

440
00:24:43.153 --> 00:24:45.120
Nate would never hurt anyone.

441
00:24:45.155 --> 00:24:48.123
That officer must be mistaken.

442
00:24:48.158 --> 00:24:49.891
Nate was the first person you healed.

443
00:24:49.927 --> 00:24:51.293
it's dangerous to go playing

444
00:24:51.328 --> 00:24:52.894
with things you don't understand.

445
00:24:52.930 --> 00:24:55.630
We're not meant to understand God's plan.

446
00:24:55.666 --> 00:24:58.200
We're meant to execute it. Do you realize

447
00:24:58.235 --> 00:25:00.702
how foolish it is to think
God gave you this power?

448
00:25:00.737 --> 00:25:02.938
This is about your glory. not God's.

449
00:25:06.243 --> 00:25:07.609
You're sick.

450
00:25:07.644 --> 00:25:10.378
Why didn't you ask me to heal you?

451
00:25:10.414 --> 00:25:11.279
Don't.

452
00:25:12.316 --> 00:25:14.382
You don't trust me.

453
00:25:14.418 --> 00:25:17.986
You've been different.

454
00:25:18.021 --> 00:25:20.989
Your head's not quiet.

455
00:25:21.024 --> 00:25:22.657
Started even

456
00:25:22.693 --> 00:25:24.426
before you got the power.

457
00:25:24.461 --> 00:25:28.096
I never paid no mind to it.
Now I can't ignore it.

458
00:25:28.131 --> 00:25:31.166
I just felt daddy's death
more deeply than you did.

459
00:25:31.201 --> 00:25:34.169
No. No. before daddy died.

460
00:25:34.204 --> 00:25:37.472
There's something you're not
telling me. This power.

461
00:25:37.508 --> 00:25:39.674
whatever you do with it.

462
00:25:39.710 --> 00:25:42.511
it won't lighten that burden.
whatever it may be.

463
00:25:42.546 --> 00:25:44.312
I need you to leave.

464
00:25:44.348 --> 00:25:47.182
And don't bother coming back to the church.

465
00:25:47.217 --> 00:25:50.619
I can't have a nonbeliever
tainting my flock.

466
00:26:07.917 --> 00:26:10.151
I need to get this guy alone.

467
00:26:10.187 --> 00:26:12.387
Have a private chat with him at his house.

468
00:26:12.422 --> 00:26:14.556
- I'll come with you.
- It's better if you stay here.

469
00:26:14.591 --> 00:26:18.293
Things could get unpleasant.

470
00:26:19.296 --> 00:26:21.229
Former girl scout. are we?

471
00:26:21.264 --> 00:26:23.932
- Not exactly.
- You know. one of these days

472
00:26:23.967 --> 00:26:26.801
you're gonna have to let me be
the mysterious one of the duo.

473
00:26:26.837 --> 00:26:28.303
One of these days.

474
00:26:28.338 --> 00:26:29.971
Remember.

475
00:26:30.006 --> 00:26:31.806
we have to save Zachary from himself.

476
00:26:31.842 --> 00:26:34.008
it's not his fault.
He thinks he's doing good.

477
00:26:34.044 --> 00:26:36.177
Well. then I'll have to impress
upon him his moral duty.

478
00:26:36.213 --> 00:26:39.814
won't I? Physically. if necessary.

479
00:26:53.563 --> 00:26:56.531
I remember you.

480
00:26:56.566 --> 00:26:58.333
You feeling all better

481
00:26:58.368 --> 00:27:01.369
- from your cold?
- Much. Ta.

482
00:27:01.405 --> 00:27:05.640
You'll have to wait until
morning and wait in line again.

483
00:27:05.675 --> 00:27:07.876
God doesn't play favorites.

484
00:27:07.911 --> 00:27:09.878
I know about the angel feather.

485
00:27:20.190 --> 00:27:21.790
Whatever your intentions.

486
00:27:21.825 --> 00:27:24.125
you're doing more harm than good.

487
00:27:24.161 --> 00:27:25.226
And you are...?

488
00:27:25.262 --> 00:27:26.694
A concerned citizen.

489
00:27:26.730 --> 00:27:28.897
You have something
that doesn't belong to you.

490
00:27:28.932 --> 00:27:30.732
and if you continue to use it.

491
00:27:30.767 --> 00:27:32.734
there will be a cost.

492
00:27:32.769 --> 00:27:35.336
not least of which will be a dead angel.

493
00:27:35.372 --> 00:27:38.473
People just love telling me what to do.

494
00:27:38.508 --> 00:27:40.008
I'm sure. How do I know

495
00:27:40.043 --> 00:27:41.910
that you'll return the feather

496
00:27:41.945 --> 00:27:44.078
to this... Angel you're
talking about instead

497
00:27:44.114 --> 00:27:45.480
of taking the power for yourself?

498
00:27:45.515 --> 00:27:46.948
That's a good point.

499
00:27:48.118 --> 00:27:49.117
Sorry in advance.

500
00:27:50.187 --> 00:27:51.486
No!

501
00:27:54.791 --> 00:27:57.759
That was the feather. not me.

502
00:27:57.794 --> 00:28:00.728
But it confirms one thing that I felt...

503
00:28:00.764 --> 00:28:03.932
You are the only evil here.

504
00:28:03.967 --> 00:28:06.701
Leave.

505
00:28:06.736 --> 00:28:09.270
And don't come back.

506
00:29:03.126 --> 00:29:05.460
- You okay?
- Yeah.

507
00:29:11.201 --> 00:29:13.434
I call them ghouls.

508
00:29:13.470 --> 00:29:15.770
They're formed by magic gone wrong.

509
00:29:15.805 --> 00:29:18.172
I recognized the one that attacked zed

510
00:29:18.208 --> 00:29:20.975
from an article online.
The preacher. he healed his leg.

511
00:29:21.011 --> 00:29:22.343
Mortals aren't meant to wield

512
00:29:22.379 --> 00:29:23.678
the power of angels.

513
00:29:23.713 --> 00:29:25.780
Nate was the first one healed.

514
00:29:25.815 --> 00:29:27.815
More will turn. just like him.

515
00:29:27.851 --> 00:29:29.918
- So why did he come after me?
- I don't think

516
00:29:29.953 --> 00:29:31.319
he was trying to kill you. luv.

517
00:29:31.354 --> 00:29:32.754
it looked to me that he was...

518
00:29:32.789 --> 00:29:34.822
Searching for something.

519
00:29:34.858 --> 00:29:36.591
When you touched Zachary. you had a vision.

520
00:29:36.626 --> 00:29:39.460
which means you took on some of his energy.

521
00:29:39.496 --> 00:29:41.796
Maybe he wanted Zachary to heal him again.

522
00:29:41.831 --> 00:29:44.265
We need to get the feather back to you.

523
00:29:44.301 --> 00:29:45.833
With the magic in its rightful place.

524
00:29:45.869 --> 00:29:48.102
it should stop the rest from turning.

525
00:29:48.138 --> 00:29:49.504
You need to work fast.

526
00:29:49.539 --> 00:29:51.339
She's getting weaker by the minute.

527
00:29:51.340 --> 00:29:52.972
Yeah. the trouble is.

528
00:29:53.007 --> 00:29:56.075
preacher Zachary has
the feather's power on his side.

529
00:29:56.111 --> 00:29:58.511
He was our friend.

530
00:29:58.546 --> 00:30:01.380
Our neighbor.

531
00:30:01.416 --> 00:30:03.382
our brother.

532
00:30:03.418 --> 00:30:06.018
But inside Nate Byars

533
00:30:06.054 --> 00:30:09.522
a darkness lay in wait.

534
00:30:09.557 --> 00:30:11.757
I offer my healing hand

535
00:30:11.793 --> 00:30:14.160
to those pure of heart.

536
00:30:14.195 --> 00:30:15.528
So we.

537
00:30:15.563 --> 00:30:18.498
powerful. may unite

538
00:30:18.533 --> 00:30:21.334
against the dark.

539
00:30:21.369 --> 00:30:24.370
Preacher. I made a huge mistake.

540
00:30:24.405 --> 00:30:26.172
I trusted the wrong man.

541
00:30:26.207 --> 00:30:28.407
See. uh. my friend John.

542
00:30:28.443 --> 00:30:30.343
he doesn't care about me

543
00:30:30.378 --> 00:30:32.578
or anything that's happening here.

544
00:30:32.614 --> 00:30:35.281
I don't even know why he came.

545
00:30:35.316 --> 00:30:37.717
And you don't want to know.

546
00:30:37.752 --> 00:30:40.353
He had a dark purpose.

547
00:30:40.388 --> 00:30:43.956
You were right about me.

548
00:30:43.992 --> 00:30:46.626
I want to believe.

549
00:30:46.661 --> 00:30:48.127
Recognizing the path you're on

550
00:30:48.163 --> 00:30:50.429
is the first step in changing direction.

551
00:30:50.465 --> 00:30:53.232
I wish I could start all over.

552
00:30:53.268 --> 00:30:56.068
if your heart is true.

553
00:30:56.104 --> 00:31:00.406
it's never too late
to surrender your will to God.

554
00:31:02.410 --> 00:31:04.343
What do you know about Baptism?

555
00:31:10.118 --> 00:31:11.584
Hallelujah!

556
00:31:11.619 --> 00:31:13.286
Hallelujah!

557
00:31:13.321 --> 00:31:15.388
Hallelujah! Praise the lord!

558
00:31:15.423 --> 00:31:17.323
Amen!

559
00:31:26.367 --> 00:31:29.769
You ready to leave
your old life behind you?

560
00:31:29.804 --> 00:31:31.304
I am.

561
00:31:31.339 --> 00:31:33.973
I baptize you now

562
00:31:34.008 --> 00:31:37.076
in front of these witnesses.

563
00:31:37.111 --> 00:31:38.411
in the name of the father

564
00:31:38.446 --> 00:31:41.180
and of the son and of the holy ghost.

565
00:31:42.784 --> 00:31:45.651
And everybody said amen!

566
00:31:45.687 --> 00:31:46.686
Amen!

567
00:31:48.957 --> 00:31:51.157
Why?

568
00:31:51.192 --> 00:31:52.925
Why would you...?

569
00:31:52.961 --> 00:31:55.361
I had to. Get off! Get off!

570
00:31:56.731 --> 00:31:58.097
Nancy.

571
00:31:58.132 --> 00:32:00.132
what's wrong?

572
00:32:05.573 --> 00:32:07.173
Everybody run!

573
00:32:15.075 --> 00:32:16.909
- Look what you've done!
- This is what we were trying to avoid!

574
00:32:16.944 --> 00:32:18.644
- Run to the church!
- Come on!

575
00:32:18.679 --> 00:32:21.146
Come on! Let's go!

576
00:32:27.955 --> 00:32:29.488
Go! Go!

577
00:32:29.523 --> 00:32:31.790
Get in there!

578
00:32:43.370 --> 00:32:45.170
They're after the feather.

579
00:32:45.206 --> 00:32:46.605
Zed. you have to get it to Imogen.

580
00:32:46.640 --> 00:32:48.006
- Go out the back.
- What about you?

581
00:32:48.042 --> 00:32:50.709
We can hold it here. Go!

582
00:32:56.383 --> 00:32:58.684
It hurts so much.

583
00:33:01.722 --> 00:33:04.923
John is your best chance
at getting that feather back.

584
00:33:06.427 --> 00:33:08.861
What...?

585
00:33:15.836 --> 00:33:17.503
What's it like?

586
00:33:19.507 --> 00:33:21.039
Pain.

587
00:33:21.075 --> 00:33:23.509
It comes in waves.

588
00:33:25.112 --> 00:33:27.179
You feel helpless.

589
00:33:27.214 --> 00:33:29.548
You can't fight it.

590
00:33:29.583 --> 00:33:32.885
It becomes about making
it to the other side.

591
00:33:32.920 --> 00:33:36.488
shrinking your world down
to one fine point.

592
00:33:36.524 --> 00:33:40.893
When that wave melts away. you feel relief.

593
00:33:40.928 --> 00:33:45.330
Just for a moment.

594
00:33:45.366 --> 00:33:47.699
till it comes back to remind you.

595
00:33:47.735 --> 00:33:51.436
So you feel pain now. but...

596
00:33:51.472 --> 00:33:53.872
What was it like

597
00:33:53.908 --> 00:33:57.776
the first moment the sun hit your skin?

598
00:33:58.946 --> 00:34:01.380
How good was that?

599
00:34:07.555 --> 00:34:08.954
Getting a little bit knackered here. mate.

600
00:34:08.989 --> 00:34:10.856
I could really use your help
about now. yeah?

601
00:34:10.891 --> 00:34:12.291
I brought this on myself.

602
00:34:12.326 --> 00:34:14.259
Look. you got a little bit of power.

603
00:34:14.295 --> 00:34:16.962
and you got off your trolley.
yeah? It happens.

604
00:34:16.997 --> 00:34:18.530
All we need to do is keep them

605
00:34:18.566 --> 00:34:20.699
at bay until Zed makes it to the angel.

606
00:34:20.734 --> 00:34:22.534
so just do us a bloody favor.

607
00:34:22.570 --> 00:34:25.470
Pull your head out of your ass
and give us a hand. yeah?

608
00:34:26.941 --> 00:34:29.241
This was never a gift from God.

609
00:34:29.276 --> 00:34:30.776
I never deserved it.

610
00:34:30.811 --> 00:34:32.244
I've sinned.

611
00:34:32.279 --> 00:34:34.146
and this here's my punishment.

612
00:34:34.181 --> 00:34:35.814
That angel gets her feather back.

613
00:34:35.849 --> 00:34:37.916
and these bastards revert back
to their mortal form.

614
00:34:37.952 --> 00:34:41.153
it should be... Any minute now!

615
00:34:41.188 --> 00:34:43.555
I had too many that night.

616
00:34:45.025 --> 00:34:48.093
It was a deer. I told myself.

617
00:34:48.128 --> 00:34:50.095
I never went back to check.

618
00:34:50.130 --> 00:34:52.431
I just left the mess behind.

619
00:34:52.466 --> 00:34:53.665
What are you saying?

620
00:34:53.701 --> 00:34:56.401
I know it wasn't a deer!

621
00:34:56.437 --> 00:34:58.604
You killed a man.

622
00:34:58.639 --> 00:35:00.906
I never told no one.

623
00:35:00.941 --> 00:35:02.407
Didn't want my daddy

624
00:35:02.443 --> 00:35:04.476
looking at me the way he always did.

625
00:35:04.511 --> 00:35:07.312
You had a mortal sin on
your soul when you nearly died.

626
00:35:07.348 --> 00:35:09.982
which means you weren't
on your way to heaven

627
00:35:10.017 --> 00:35:12.184
when you saw the angel.

628
00:35:12.219 --> 00:35:14.319
You were on your way to hell.

629
00:35:16.056 --> 00:35:17.990
They're taking too long.

630
00:35:18.025 --> 00:35:20.259
Will John come through?

631
00:35:20.294 --> 00:35:22.661
if it serves him.

632
00:35:22.696 --> 00:35:26.198
Self-interest is natural for them.

633
00:35:26.233 --> 00:35:28.834
You noticed. too?

634
00:35:28.869 --> 00:35:31.970
Right. they have no idea
the gift they were given

635
00:35:32.006 --> 00:35:34.973
when they got this world.

636
00:35:35.009 --> 00:35:36.608
We would have done better.

637
00:35:36.644 --> 00:35:38.343
Do you believe that?

638
00:35:38.379 --> 00:35:39.978
Of course.

639
00:35:40.014 --> 00:35:41.613
it's why we were put here.

640
00:35:41.649 --> 00:35:44.349
He gave them free will
to stand on their own.

641
00:35:44.385 --> 00:35:47.219
but all they do is fall

642
00:35:47.254 --> 00:35:49.288
over and over...

643
00:35:49.323 --> 00:35:51.456
And over and

644
00:35:51.492 --> 00:35:55.060
over and over.

645
00:35:55.095 --> 00:35:58.196
We're nothing but crutches
for his flawed creation.

646
00:35:58.232 --> 00:36:01.400
We shouldn't be talking like this.

647
00:36:01.435 --> 00:36:03.235
Why not?

648
00:36:03.270 --> 00:36:04.836
I want this world back. Manny.

649
00:36:06.240 --> 00:36:07.906
Just for ourselves.

650
00:36:09.043 --> 00:36:10.509
I got it!

651
00:36:12.946 --> 00:36:14.913
You really think I was headed to hell?

652
00:36:14.948 --> 00:36:18.848
Zed... we can't let her
give that feather to Imogen.

653
00:36:18.948 --> 00:36:20.481
We have to stop her.

654
00:36:27.523 --> 00:36:30.291
Let's go.

655
00:36:30.326 --> 00:36:32.326
I deserve it!

656
00:37:02.725 --> 00:37:04.658
This is not good.

657
00:37:08.965 --> 00:37:11.365
it worked.

658
00:37:15.338 --> 00:37:17.137
Beautifully.

659
00:37:25.815 --> 00:37:27.514
You're fallen.

660
00:37:34.815 --> 00:37:36.283
I have to admit. I thought a ghoul

661
00:37:36.315 --> 00:37:38.982
would deliver me the feather.
but thank you. Zed.

662
00:37:52.698 --> 00:37:54.264
Looks like my protection spell

663
00:37:54.300 --> 00:37:56.367
to keep evil out is keeping evil in.

664
00:37:58.137 --> 00:38:00.137
A fallen angel finds a desperate bloke.

665
00:38:00.172 --> 00:38:02.306
intercepts him at the gates of hell

666
00:38:02.341 --> 00:38:03.941
and makes him think
it's the gates of heaven.

667
00:38:03.976 --> 00:38:07.611
Zachary didn't take your feather.

668
00:38:07.646 --> 00:38:10.581
You put it in his hand so you
could break through to earth.

669
00:38:10.616 --> 00:38:13.150
The ghouls were after the
feather to bring it back to you?

670
00:38:13.185 --> 00:38:14.818
You make it sound so easy.

671
00:38:14.854 --> 00:38:17.187
I faked the heavenly angel part.

672
00:38:17.223 --> 00:38:19.690
Pain... That was real.

673
00:38:19.725 --> 00:38:22.593
Hell must have prepared you well.
I'll never go back there.

674
00:38:22.628 --> 00:38:25.195
Lift the spell. or I will kill her.

675
00:38:25.231 --> 00:38:26.497
I deserve to be out there.

676
00:38:26.532 --> 00:38:29.767
I served loyally for lifetimes.

677
00:38:29.802 --> 00:38:30.723
Then I was cast

678
00:38:30.802 --> 00:38:32.770
out of heaven for one indiscretion.

679
00:38:32.805 --> 00:38:34.805
What did you do?

680
00:38:34.840 --> 00:38:37.307
I killed a mortal.

681
00:38:37.902 --> 00:38:39.068
I wanted to see

682
00:38:39.103 --> 00:38:40.769
how easy it would be.

683
00:38:42.273 --> 00:38:43.839
You're the only one who can stop this.

684
00:38:43.873 --> 00:38:45.005
You know I can't.

685
00:38:45.040 --> 00:38:46.473
You mean you won't.

686
00:38:46.475 --> 00:38:49.476
Help her!

687
00:38:49.512 --> 00:38:52.880
You're either in this bloody
fight with me. or you're not.

688
00:38:52.915 --> 00:38:54.548
Come on.

689
00:38:56.285 --> 00:38:58.472
You know the rules!

690
00:38:58.485 --> 00:38:59.784
Manny!

691
00:39:00.387 --> 00:39:01.887
Guess you are on your own.

692
00:39:02.287 --> 00:39:04.954
Your angel did what they always do...

693
00:39:04.989 --> 00:39:05.988
Nothing!

694
00:39:06.024 --> 00:39:08.591
Like hell.

695
00:39:28.551 --> 00:39:30.284
John?

696
00:39:30.320 --> 00:39:32.587
What is this?

697
00:39:32.622 --> 00:39:34.155
No.

698
00:39:34.190 --> 00:39:36.023
You don't want to hold
that for too long. luv.

699
00:39:36.059 --> 00:39:37.492
That's concentrated evil.

700
00:39:39.696 --> 00:39:43.664
I know I've disappointed
more than a few of you.

701
00:39:43.700 --> 00:39:47.401
Got amends to make.

702
00:39:50.507 --> 00:39:54.342
I've. uh. felt the light of an angel

703
00:39:54.377 --> 00:39:56.978
and the hand of the devil.

704
00:39:57.013 --> 00:40:01.115
Though those are forces
much greater than we are.

705
00:40:01.151 --> 00:40:03.117
the only thing

706
00:40:03.153 --> 00:40:08.289
more powerful is our ability to choose.

707
00:40:08.324 --> 00:40:13.227
if you'll open your hymnals to page 64.

708
00:40:13.263 --> 00:40:16.464
"all glory be thine."

709
00:40:16.499 --> 00:40:18.666
The preacher's back in his church.

710
00:40:18.701 --> 00:40:21.536
still fighting desperately
to make amends for his sin.

711
00:40:21.571 --> 00:40:23.337
for the mistake that haunts him.

712
00:40:23.373 --> 00:40:25.706
hoping it's not too late
to change his fate.

713
00:40:25.742 --> 00:40:27.141
Do you really think

714
00:40:27.177 --> 00:40:30.077
the preacher and I have anything in common?

715
00:40:30.113 --> 00:40:32.914
You should know by now
I don't have all the answers.

716
00:40:32.949 --> 00:40:36.150
She fooled us all. mate.

717
00:40:36.186 --> 00:40:38.386
And that's not something
I admit to lightly.

718
00:40:38.421 --> 00:40:40.822
There's just

719
00:40:40.857 --> 00:40:44.492
one thing I can't wrap my head
around. though. and that's...

720
00:40:44.527 --> 00:40:47.562
How the bloody hell
she managed to break through.

721
00:40:47.597 --> 00:40:50.198
The barrier between hell and
earth is getting thinner. John.

722
00:40:50.233 --> 00:40:54.702
Thinner than it's ever been.

723
00:40:54.737 --> 00:40:57.939
Consequence of the rising darkness?

724
00:41:04.614 --> 00:41:07.321
But you saved the day.

725
00:41:07.414 --> 00:41:08.914
That's the kind of faith I can get behind.

726
00:41:09.414 --> 00:41:11.214
I will face consequences of my action.

727
00:41:11.614 --> 00:41:14.614
- But. what Imogen did...
- Shouldn't have been possible.

728
00:41:15.493 --> 00:41:17.326
Seems anything that has the will

729
00:41:17.361 --> 00:41:19.261
to leave hell will find a way.

730
00:41:21.766 --> 00:41:24.233
But when they do.

731
00:41:24.268 --> 00:41:26.635
we'll be waiting for them.

732
00:41:38.182 --> 00:41:40.316
Hello.

733
00:41:40.351 --> 00:41:42.651
Don't tell me there's
another Giancarlo's in town.

734
00:41:44.155 --> 00:41:45.788
Eddie.

735
00:41:47.291 --> 00:41:49.291
I completely forgot.

736
00:41:49.327 --> 00:41:51.160
Oh. I... I can wait if you want.

737
00:41:51.195 --> 00:41:53.195
I'm so sorry.

738
00:41:53.231 --> 00:41:57.266
I just don't know
if I'll be any good tonight.

739
00:41:57.301 --> 00:41:59.001
Can we do this some other time?

740
00:41:59.036 --> 00:42:00.869
Yeah. of course.

741
00:42:00.905 --> 00:42:04.640
Thank you. Um. I'm sorry
you came all that way.

742
00:42:04.675 --> 00:42:07.676
It's no problem at all.
Take the time you need.

743
00:42:07.712 --> 00:42:09.278
Thanks.

744
00:42:09.313 --> 00:42:10.746
Bye.

745
00:42:14.185 --> 00:42:17.489
- She's not coming.
- Not tonight.

746
00:42:19.289 --> 00:42:20.785
Soon. then.
